Doesn't seem to be compatible with Vista. (Surprised anyone?) I've downloaded the same app from 2 torrents, and after what seems to be a clean install when I run it I'm told that some files have failed to write to registry. There's no mention of Vista support on the website.

I'm not sure what that .message file contains, I hope it's not the password because I chose to deselect it... But those of you experiencing trouble with this torrent due to that file, are you by any chance on a computer with a Fat harddrive?. I believe that the old style 8 character filename, which still resides within the fat32 even though transparent to the user, might have some issues when it comes to files which it interprets to not have a name, just an extension.
